   "source": [
    "# Values of 'INCOME_TOTAL\" and \"CREDIT\" were only normalized because they were the only continous data type columns\n",
    "\n",
    "mean_income = df['INCOME_TOTAL'].mean()\n",
    "std_income = df['INCOME_TOTAL'].std()\n",
    "mean_credit = df['CREDIT'].mean()\n",
    "std_credit = df['CREDIT'].std()\n",
    "\n",
    "df['INCOME_TOTAL'] = df['INCOME_TOTAL'] - mean_income\n",
    "df['INCOME_TOTAL'] = df['INCOME_TOTAL'] / std_income\n",
    "\n",
    "df['CREDIT'] = df['CREDIT'] - mean_credit\n",
    "df['CREDIT'] =  df['CREDIT'] / std_credit\n",
    "\n",
    "df"
   ]

    "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\n",
    "gle = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "columns = ['NAME_CONTRACT_TYPE','CODE_GENDER','FLAG_OWN_CAR','FLAG_OWN_REALTY','NAME_INCOME_TYPE','EDUCATION_TYPE','FAMILY_STATUS','HOUSING_TYPE','OCCUPATION_TYPE','ORGANIZATION_TYPE']\n",
    "new_cols = ['NAME_CONTRACT_TYPE_n','CODE_GENDER_n','FLAG_OWN_CAR_n','FLAG_OWN_REALTY_n','NAME_INCOME_TYPE_n','EDUCATION_TYPE_n','FAMILY_STATUS_n','HOUSING_TYPE_n','OCCUPATION_TYPE_n','ORGANIZATION_TYPE_n']\n",
    "for c,col in enumerate(columns):\n",
    "    labels = gle.fit_transform(df[col])\n",
    "    df[col] = labels\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]

    "Negative correlation means increase in one's value decreases other's value<br>\n",

    "Positive correlation means increase in one's value increase other's value\n"
